title: Incumbent Kagame votes in Rwanda election
description:
(4 Aug 2017) Rwandan President Paul Kagame on Friday cast his vote in a presidential election where he is widely expected to win. 
Kagame, who won the 2010 election with 93 percent of the vote, told a rally in July that "the day of the presidential elections will just be a formality".
He is running against Frank Habineza of the Democratic Green Party of Rwanda - the only permitted opposition party - and independent candidate Philippe Mpayimana.
